@description.name: @description
@description.body: Mixin that provides the functionality for a dialog with a form that is constructed on-the-fly. Used by the Window-based dialog form, and by an embedded dialog form

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Allow disabling autocomplete on all text and password fields

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Data to create a form with multiple fields. So far implemented: TextField / TextArea ComboBox SelectBox RadioGroup CheckBox Spinner List 

 {
  "username" : {
     'type'  : "TextField",
     'label' : "User Name",
     'value' : ""
   },
   "address" : {
     'type'  : "TextArea",
     'label' : "Address",
     'lines' : 3
   },
   "domain" : {
     'type'  : "SelectBox",
     'label' : "Domain",
     'value' : 1,
     'options' : [
       { 'label' : "Company", 'value' : 0 },
       { 'label' : "Home",    'value' : 1 }
     ]
   },
   "commands" : {
    'type'  : "ComboBox",
     'label' : "Shell command to execute",
     'options' : [
       { 'label' : "ln -s *" },
       { 'label' : "rm -Rf /" }
     ]
   },
   "quantity" : {
    'type' : "Spinner",
    'label' : "How many?",
    'properties' : {
      'minimum' : 1,
      'maximum' : 20,
      'maxWidth' : 100
    }
   }
 }

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The model of the result data

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The default width of the column with the field labels

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Function to call to create and configure a form renderer. If null, a single-column form renderer is automatically instantiated and configured. The function is passed a single argument, the form object.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Function to call just before creating the form's input fields. This allows additional, non-form widgets to be added. The function is called two arguments: the container in which the form fields should be placed, and the form object itself (this).

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Function to call with the internal form, allowing the user to do things such as set up a form validator (vs. field validators) on the form. The function is called with two arguments: the internal qx.ui.form.Form object, and the current dialog.Form object. An attempt is made to call the function in the context specified in the form data, but that may not work properly if the context property is not yet set at the time at the form is created.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Function to call just after creating the form's input fields. This allows additional, non-form widgets to be added. The function is called one two arguments: the container in which the form fields should be placed, and the form object itself (this).

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Function to call just after creating the form's buttons. This allows additional, additional widgets to be added. The function is called with two arguments: the container in which the buttons were placed, and the form object itself (this).

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Function to call just after the form is filled with data. The function is called with one argument: the form object itself (this).

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Register a form element to be used within a qxl.dialog form.

@param.name: @param
@param.description: The field type, later to be used as the type member when setting the fieldData property.

@param.name: @param
@param.body: handlers {Map} Handler functions for this form element. initElement is mandatory; addToFormController and postProcess are optional. All handlers are called in the context of the qxl.dialog.Form or qxl.dialog.FormEmbed. The fieldType argument has already been down-cased upon call. - initElement(fieldType, fieldData) Instantiate and initialize the form field to be used on the form.
@param.description: Handler functions for this form element. initElement is mandatory; addToFormController and postProcess are optional.
